      "writtenOn": "2020-10-29T17:11:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Let\u0027s land the first iteration with out rcp/rsqrt contamination. I also renamed \"madd\" to \"fast_fma\" to (hopefully) draw more attention to the fact that its behavior is platform dependent.\n\nI have two possible use-cases in mind for rsqrt/rcp.\n\n  1. Use rcp in fast_acos. Bumps error from .96 to 1.25 degrees.\n\n  2. Use \"rsqrt(rsqrt(max(x,epsilon)))\" in Wang\u0027s formula instead of \"sqrt(sqrt(x))\". Preliminary testing shows that the rsqrt version still gets us within a fraction of a tessellation segment.\n\nBut let\u0027s first dig around for some better documentation and do a more formal perf analysis once stroking is closer to complete before committing to these instructions.",
      "parentUuid": "9f62480c_f9257304",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 20,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 20,
        "endChar": 32
      },
