      "writtenOn": "2020-10-28T15:09:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The minimum precision of these intrinsics is spec\u0027d on intel, but not the maximum, and the intrinsics sometimes generate different instructions depending on compiler settings.  Even the same instruction can deliver different results on different CPUs, most easily seen running on AMD CPUs, but even between Intel chips.\n\nI suspect the situation for ARM (with even more chip diversity) is worse than that, but I don\u0027t know it off the top of my head.",
      "parentUuid": "8add1963_dfc3a28e",
      "range": {
